AN ABBREVIATION ALREADY.

22:20.600 --> 22:22.193
OK, I WONDER IF HE KNOWS
ABOUT SPENCER, THOUGH.

22:22.200 --> 22:24.510
ARE YOU

22:24.510 --> 22:26.103
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

22:26.110 --> 22:27.464
SPENCER IS NOT OUR BROTHER.

22:27.470 --> 22:29.472
AND THE FACT THAT GW WAS
AT THE ADDRESS

22:29.480 --> 22:31.141
DISPROVES YOUR
ENTIRE THEORY.

22:31.150 --> 22:32.902
MAYBE, MAYBE NOT.

22:32.910 --> 22:35.117
EITHER WAY, DAD'S STILL LYING
ABOUT HIS HISTORY WITH GRACE,

22:35.120 --> 22:36.918
AND WE HAVE
TO FIND OUT WHY.

22:36.920 --> 22:38.149
NO, WE DON'T.

22:38.150 --> 22:39.481
MAN: AND NOW IT'S
UP TO YOU, COME ON

22:39.490 --> 22:41.788
WE GOING ALL NIGHT...

22:41.790 --> 22:46.455
SO ASHER WAS ALL,
"NO! PLEASE! NO!"

22:46.460 --> 22:49.122
ALL RIGHT. YOU'RE
EXAGGERATING A BIT.

22:49.130 --> 22:50.620
IT WAS CRAZY.

22:50.630 --> 22:53.668
THE CAR JUST KEPT ROLLING
RIGHT OUT INTO THE STREET.

22:53.670 --> 22:55.866
THAT'S BECAUSE YOU FORGOT
TO PUT THE PARKING BRAKE ON.

22:55.870 --> 22:57.565
ALL RIGHT.
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

22:57.570 --> 22:59.129
WHY ARE WE EVEN TALKING
ABOUT THIS? IT'S FIXED.

22:59.140 --> 23:00.460
MOVE ON.

23:00.470 --> 23:02.131
JJ: WHERE'D YOU TAKE IT?

23:02.140 --> 23:03.232
I KNOW A GUY.

23:03.240 --> 23:04.776
<i>33: YOU KNOW A GUY
WHO CAN FIX</i>

23:04.780 --> 23:09.320
A 1959 PORSCHE ROADSTER
IN ONE DAY?

23:09.320 --> 23:11.914
I DON'T SEE IT.

23:11.920 --> 23:13.149
ONE DAY, DUDE?

23:13.150 --> 23:18.020
HEY. MONEY TALKS, BOYS.

23:18.030 --> 23:20.385
I WHIPPED OUT MY DAD'S
BLACK CARD. BOOM.

23:20.390 --> 23:22.927
NEXT DAY, GOOD AS NEW.

23:29.640 --> 23:31.460
SO HOW COME YOU AIN'T
BRING YOUR GIRL?

23:31.470 --> 23:34.064
