COULD SOMEONE PLEASE TELL ME
WHAT THE HELL IS

25:37.100 --> 25:38.192
GOING ON HERE.

25:38.200 --> 25:40.669
AND WHY, FOR THE LOVE OF GOD,
IS YOUR FATHER

25:40.670 --> 25:42.331
IN OUR LIVING ROOM?

25:42.340 --> 25:44.331
YOUR GUESS IS AS GOOD
AS MINE.

25:44.340 --> 25:46.399
SPILL IT NOW...

25:46.410 --> 25:47.730
OR ELSE!

25:47.740 --> 25:50.675
IF YOU WANT TO KNOW,
YOU GOT TO ASK.

25:52.610 --> 25:55.147
IS SPENCER OUR BROTHER?

26:03.890 --> 26:07.428
YOU TWO THINK THAT I'M
SPENCER'S FATHER?

26:07.430 --> 26:09.319
NO, I DIDN'T.

26:09.330 --> 26:10.593
AND THEN I DID.

26:10.600 --> 26:13.399
AND NOW I-- I DON'T
KNOW WHAT TO THINK.

26:13.400 --> 26:15.732
IT WAS
JORDAN'S THEORY.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.265
NICE. THANKS A LOT.

26:17.270 --> 26:19.534
ENLIGHTEN US,
JORDAN.

26:19.540 --> 26:21.634
OK, YOU MOVED SPENCER
INTO OUR HOME.

26:21.640 --> 26:22.937
LOOK, HOLD UP. HOLD UP.

26:22.940 --> 26:24.806
I HAD NO CHOICE BECAUSE
YOU TRIED

26:24.810 --> 26:26.448
TO BLOCK HIS TRANSFER TO
BEVERLY HILLS.

26:26.450 --> 26:27.940
AND THEN AT THE BARBER SHOP,

26:27.950 --> 26:30.009
I FOUND OUT YOU HAD
A PAST WITH HIS MOM.

26:30.020 --> 26:31.840
SORRY YOU HAD TO FIND OUT
THIS WAY, MOM,

26:31.850 --> 26:33.215
BUT--BUT DAD,
HE AND GRACE HAD--

26:33.220 --> 26:35.382
I KNOW. THEY DATED
IN HIGH SCHOOL. I KNOW.

26:35.390 --> 26:37.313
IS THAT YOUR BOMBSHELL
EVIDENCE?

26:37.320 --> 26:38.526
OLIVIA: WELL, I MEAN,

26:38.530 --> 26:40.180
YOU WERE MAKING PAYMENTS
FOR 17 YEARS,

26:40.190 --> 26:42.454
AND WE THOUGHT THAT IT
WAS CHILD SUPPORT,

26:42.460 --> 26:45.100
BUT THE ADDRESS LED US
TO GRANDPA.

26:45.100 --> 26:48.365
EXACTLY. AND HE'S
IN MY HOUSE NOW.

26:48.370 --> 26:49.633
SORRY.

26:49.640 --> 26:51.096
LAURA: I'M SPEECHLESS.

26:51.100 --> 26:53.364
YOU TWO ARE THE WORST DETECTIVES
IN THE WORLD.

26:53.370 --> 26:54.838
BILLY: THE WORST.

26:54.840 --> 26:56.205
THE INVESTIGATION
WAS FLAWED.

26:56.210 --> 26:57.848
OK, WE GOT IT.
SO JUST TO BE CLEAR,

26:57.850 --> 26:59.739
YOU'RE NOT SPENCER'S
FATHER?

26:59.750 --> 27:00.808
BILLY: JORDAN, NO.

27:00.810 --> 27:03.370
I AM NOT SPENCER'S DAD.

27:03.380 --> 27:05.382
I TOLD YOU.

27:05.390 --> 27:08.155
OK. WELL, UM, YOU KNOW,

27:08.160 --> 27:10.288
I SAY WE PUT THIS LITTLE
MISUNDERSTANDING BEHIND US

27:10.290 --> 27:11.519
AND GO GET SOME CAKE.

27:11.530 --> 27:12.782
-YUP.
-UH, NO.

27:12.790 --> 27:14.383
BILLY: MM-MM, MM-MM.

27:14.390 --> 27:15.425
THIS CASE WILL
REMAIN OPEN

27:15.430 --> 27:16.591
UNTIL WE DETERMINE

27:16.600 --> 27:18.159
THE APPROPRIATE
PUNISHMENT,

27:18.170 --> 27:19.399
BUT UNTIL THEN,

27:19.400 --> 27:20.925
WE HAVE GUESTS!

27:20.930 --> 27:25.208
SO COULD EVERYBODY JUST SMILE?

27:33.910 --> 27:35.776
WILLIE: A STRANGE
BUNCH THERE, HUH?

27:35.780 --> 27:37.316
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

27:37.320 --> 27:39.243
SPENCER JAMES?

27:39.250 --> 27:41.412
-HEH HEH!

27:41.420 --> 27:43.149
NO, BUT I KNOW YOU.

27:43.160 --> 27:44.889
YOU'RE ALL THE TALK AROUND
THE NEIGHBORHOOD THESE DAYS.

27:44.890 --> 27:47.723
SOUTH CRENSHAW'S STAR
WIDE RECEIVER

27:47.730 --> 27:49.824
BOOKING IT TO BEVERLY.

27:49.830 --> 27:53.528
HMM. ONE OF BILLY'S
BOYS NOW, HMM?

27:53.530 --> 27:54.964
THAT'S RIGHT.

27:54.970 --> 27:56.631
SO YOU HERE
FOR THE PARTY?

27:56.640 --> 27:57.937
THE PARTY'S FOR ME,
ACTUALLY.

27:57.940 --> 28:00.659
IT'S MY BIRTHDAY,
AND I LIVE HERE.

28:00.670 --> 28:03.970
IS THAT RIGHT?

28:05.950 --> 28:08.442
I'M SORRY. I AIN'T
CATCH YOUR NAME.

28:08.450 --> 28:12.239
WILLIE, WILLIE BAKER.

28:12.250 --> 28:15.288
I'M BILLY'S DAD.

28:15.290 --> 28:17.110
I THOUGHT YOU ALL TWO
DIDN'T SPEAK.

28:17.120 --> 28:20.454
WE DON'T. HAVEN'T
IN A LONG TIME, ANYWAY,

28:20.460 --> 28:22.952
NOT SINCE HE MARRIED LAURA.

28:22.960 --> 28:26.828
IF ONLY HE COULD'VE
HELD ON TO YOUR MOM.

28:26.830 --> 28:28.832
WAIT. MY MOM
AND COACH BAKER?

28:28.840 --> 28:31.866
OH, YEAH, MAN!
THEY WERE THICK AS THIEVES

28:31.870 --> 28:33.269
ALL THROUGH HIGH SCHOOL.

28:33.270 --> 28:35.272
THOUGHT FOR SURE THEY WERE
GONNA END UP TOGETHER.

28:35.280 --> 28:39.808
NEVER SEEN TWO KIDS
SO MUCH IN LOVE.

28:44.380 --> 28:45.484
HEY.

28:45.490 --> 28:47.481
HEY.

28:47.490 --> 28:49.959
HAVE WE BEEN HERE
LONG ENOUGH?

28:49.960 --> 28:52.429
I WASN'T TIMING
OUR ATTENDANCE.

28:52.430 --> 28:53.750
WELL, I'M READY TO GO.

28:53.760 --> 28:55.194
ARE YOU SURE? I DON'T
THINK EVERYBODY

28:55.200 --> 28:57.328
AT THE PARTY'S HEARD
ABOUT DADDY'S BLACK CARDS.

28:57.330 --> 29:00.664
I TOLD YOU TODAY 1 DID NOT
WANT TO BE A PART OF THIS.

29:00.670 --> 29:02.490
AND--AND YOU WEREN'T.

29:02.500 --> 29:03.990
WHEN YOU EMBELLISH AND--

29:04.000 --> 29:05.104
JUST SAY THE WORD.

29:05.110 --> 29:06.862
WHEN YOU LIE AND I
KNOW ABOUT IT,

29:06.870 --> 29:08.872
IT MAKES ME COMPLICIT
IN THE LIE,

29:08.880 --> 29:11.770
AND IT'S EMBARRASSING
TO WATCH.

29:11.780 --> 29:13.544
SORRY THAT MY LIFE
EMBARRASSES YOU.

29:13.550 --> 29:14.847
THAT'S NOT WHAT I SAID.

29:14.850 --> 29:17.171
YOU DO WHAT YOU WANT.

29:22.920 --> 29:24.388
-LAURA.
-HI, WILLIE.

29:24.390 --> 29:27.519
HOPE YOU DON'T MIND ME
CRASHING YOUR PARTY LIKE THIS.

29:28.660 --> 29:30.799
WE'RE FAMILY.

29:30.800 --> 29:33.019
I SEE YOU BOUGHT
A NEW HOUSE.

29:33.030 --> 29:36.034
UH, NO. WE'VE BEEN
HERE FOR A WHILE NOW.

29:36.040 --> 29:38.509
HMM. WHAT WAS WRONG
WITH THE OLD ONE?

29:38.510 --> 29:40.535
NOT BIG ENOUGH FOR YOU?

29:41.640 --> 29:43.369
CAN'T WAIT TO SEE
THE NEXT ONE.

29:44.710 --> 29:46.508
YOUR FATHER WAS JUST
ADMIRING OUR HOUSE.

29:46.510 --> 29:48.410
I WAS. IMPRESSIVE.

29:48.420 --> 29:51.446
YOU'RE REALLY LIVING THE
O.J. LIFE NOW, AREN'T YOU, SON?

29:58.390 --> 30:00.586
YOU JUST CAN'T HELP
YOURSELF, CAN YOU?

30:00.590 --> 30:02.297
HA HA!

30:02.300 --> 30:04.098
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
GET UP OUT OF HERE.

30:04.100 --> 30:05.693
-HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY. I--
-COME ON, MAN. LET'S GO.

30:05.700 --> 30:07.566
I JUST GOT HERE.

30:07.570 --> 30:09.789
LET'S GO.

30:12.140 --> 30:15.235
SO I GUESS FAMILY
ISN'T ALWAYS WELCOME.

30:15.240 --> 30:17.038
BILLY: IT'S
A PRIVATE PARTY.

30:17.040 --> 30:18.906
-SPENCER, STAY OUT OF THIS.

30:18.910 --> 30:20.173
YOU AIN'T SEEN
YOUR DAD IN YEARS,

30:20.180 --> 30:21.648
AND NOW HERE HE IS
MAKING AN EFFORT?

30:21.650 --> 30:23.049
YOU DON'T KNOW
OUR HISTORY, SON.

30:23.050 --> 30:24.370
LET'S BE STRAIGHT
HERE, COACH.

30:24.380 --> 30:25.814
IS IT HIS HISTORY
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT

30:25.820 --> 30:27.640
OR THE ONE YOU GOT
WITH MY MOM?

30:27.650 --> 30:29.789
GRACE: THAT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO.

30:29.790 --> 30:32.054
SO WHY YOU AIN'T
TELL ME?

30:37.900 --> 30:39.698
I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO KNOW IT WAS MY IDEA,

30:39.700 --> 30:41.395
YOU TRANSFERRING TO BEVERLY.

30:41.400 --> 30:43.732
I THOUGHT IF YOU KNEW BILLY
AND I HAD A PAST TOGETHER--

30:43.740 --> 30:46.539
SO YOU LIED TO ME?

30:51.110 --> 30:53.477
AND YOU TOLD ME NOT
TO GO SEE MY DAD,

30:53.480 --> 30:55.812
BUT THAT'S BECAUSE HE'D
HAVE TOLD ME

30:55.820 --> 30:57.276
ABOUT YOU AND MY MOM, RIGHT,

30:57.280 --> 31:00.614
THAT HE WAS GONNA
TELL ME THE TRUTH?

31:00.620 --> 31:02.179
RIGHT?

31:09.700 --> 31:12.499
WHY DON'T NOBODY LOOK
SURPRISED?

31:16.740 --> 31:18.799
I'M OUT.

31:18.810 --> 31:20.562
WHERE YOU GOING?

31:20.570 --> 31:22.334
DAD MAY HAVE LEFT,

31:22.340 --> 31:26.470
BUT AT LEAST HE NEVER
LIED TO ME LIKE THIS.

31:29.850 --> 31:32.285
I GOT TICKETS
TO A FOOTBALL GAME.

32:05.420 --> 32:07.787
I'M LOOKING FOR
COREY JAMES.

32:07.790 --> 32:10.009
WHO'S ASKING?

32:11.890 --> 32:14.951
HIS SON.

32:41.090 --> 32:42.717
LOOK, IF YOU CAME TO TRY
AND STOP ME

32:42.720 --> 32:44.085
FROM TALKING TO MY DAD,

32:44.090 --> 32:45.455
YOU COULD'VE SAVED
YOURSELF THE TRIP.

32:45.460 --> 32:47.224
HE DON'T WORK FOR
EASTERN NEVADA NO MORE.

32:47.230 --> 32:50.723
THE COACH TOLD ME
HE MOVED BACK TO L.A.

32:50.730 --> 32:53.768
SO I GUESS HE STILL DON'T
WANT TO SEE ME, HUH?

32:53.770 --> 32:58.310
HEY. I'M SORRY
TO HEAR THAT.

32:59.670 --> 33:01.308
YOU AIN'T THE ONLY ONE.

33:03.740 --> 33:06.175
SPENCER, WAIT UP.

33:15.660 --> 33:19.085
SO HOW WAS WORK?

33:20.760 --> 33:21.693
I--

33:21.700 --> 33:24.260
I WASN'T AT WORK.

33:24.260 --> 33:26.763
I WENT TO SPENCER'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY

33:26.770 --> 33:29.091
IN BEVERLY HILLS.

33:29.100 --> 33:30.898
I'M SORRY I LIED.

33:30.900 --> 33:32.868
WHY WOULD YOU DO THAT?

33:34.510 --> 33:37.775
I WAS AFRAID YOU'D
ASK TO GO.

33:39.180 --> 33:42.810
NOT BECAUSE I'M
ASHAMED OF YOU,

33:42.820 --> 33:46.120
BUT BECAUSE I'M
ASHAMED OF ME.

33:46.120 --> 33:49.158
MY MOM PUT ME OUT
BECAUSE OF WHO I AM.

33:49.160 --> 33:53.984
AND DEEP DOWN
INSIDE, I FELT LIKE

33:53.990 --> 33:55.526
MAYBE SHE'S RIGHT
ABOUT ME.

33:55.530 --> 33:59.296
I REALIZED TONIGHT
THAT YOU'VE

33:59.300 --> 34:01.997
BEEN THERE FOR ME
IN WAYS

34:02.000 --> 34:04.469
THAT VERY FEW PEOPLE
HAVE EVER BEEN.

34:06.110 --> 34:07.805
AND I DON'T--
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE

34:07.810 --> 34:09.733
YOUR PATIENCE.

34:11.810 --> 34:14.302
I JUST FOUND YOU.

34:16.520 --> 34:18.818
I DON'T WANT TO HIDE
THAT ANYMORE.

34:18.820 --> 34:21.687
YOU THINK YOU COULD

34:21.690 --> 34:23.658
HELP ME WITH THAT?

34:25.690 --> 34:29.728
YEAH. I THINK I
CAN HELP YOU WITH THAT.

34:29.730 --> 34:32.824
MAN: GO, BABY,
FLY TO THE PLACE

34:32.830 --> 34:34.867
I KNOW

34:34.870 --> 34:37.339
IT'S WHO I AM...

34:37.340 --> 34:39.559
YOU KNOW WHY I WANTED
TO COME HERE?

34:42.040 --> 34:46.500
I WANTED TO LET GO
OF MY DAD.

34:46.510 --> 34:48.945
I WANTED TO TELL HIM
THAT I'M MY OWN MAN

34:48.949 --> 34:51.317
AND I DON'T NEED
TO KNOW WHY HE LEFT.

34:53.520 --> 34:58.788
I WANTED TO TELL HIM
THAT I DID ALL OF THIS,

35:00.090 --> 35:05.563
THAT I BECAME THE MAN
THAT I AM ON MY OWN.

35:08.230 --> 35:10.870
AT LEAST I THOUGHT
I DID.

35:10.870 --> 35:13.532
AND YOU ARE YOUR OWN MAN.

35:14.810 --> 35:17.108
AND YOU'RE A DAMN FINE ONE,

35:17.110 --> 35:20.546
BUT YOU CAN'T ALWAYS
DO IT ON YOUR OWN.

35:22.880 --> 35:24.814
YOU NEED A TEAM...

35:27.020 --> 35:29.557
A FAMILY.

35:31.420 --> 35:33.752
AND I'M HOPING THAT YOU
CHOOSE TO BE

35:33.760 --> 35:35.558
A PART OF MINE...

35:39.130 --> 35:42.031
'CAUSE I'VE ALREADY
CHOSEN YOU.

35:42.040 --> 35:46.329
MAN: WILL YOU REACH OUT

35:46.340 --> 35:50.834
AND KEEP ME SANE?

35:55.320 --> 35:58.278
-HI.
-GOOD MORNING.

36:00.820 --> 36:03.585
LISTEN, UM...

36:05.190 --> 36:06.954
YOU WERE RIGHT,
YOU KNOW?

36:08.430 --> 36:10.694
I SHOULD HAVE JUST
LEFT IT ALONE.

36:10.700 --> 36:15.763
ACTUALLY, YOU WERE
THE ONE WHO WAS RIGHT.

36:17.600 --> 36:20.308
THE TRUTH MAY NOT
ALWAYS FEEL GOOD,

36:20.310 --> 36:23.439
BUT IT'S THE ONLY WAY
TO MOVE FORWARD.

36:27.050 --> 36:30.645
I'M SORRY WE'RE NOT
CLOSE ANYMORE.

36:30.650 --> 36:32.345
NO, THAT'S--THAT'S
MY FAULT.

36:32.350 --> 36:34.409
NO, IT'S NOT. IT'S MINE.

36:34.420 --> 36:36.286
I LET YOU THINK OTHERWISE,

36:36.290 --> 36:38.679
AND I LET EVERYONE ELSE
THINK IT, EVEN MYSELF,

36:38.690 --> 36:41.899
BUT I'M THE ONE
WHO PULLED AWAY.

36:43.960 --> 36:45.621
WHY?

36:50.040 --> 36:51.530
'CAUSE OF WHAT I DID.

36:51.540 --> 36:54.999
BECAUSE I WAS
SO TERRIFIED OF LOSING

36:55.010 --> 36:56.978
THE PEOPLE I LOVE
OVER A MISTAKE

36:56.980 --> 36:59.745
I CAN BARELY EVEN REMEMBER.

37:03.220 --> 37:04.676
LAST YEAR, I GOT WASTED,

37:04.680 --> 37:08.651
AND I DID SOMETHING
I SERIOUSLY REGRET.

37:12.890 --> 37:17.657
I...I SLEPT WITH ASHER.

37:19.070 --> 37:20.299
HE'S--

37:20.300 --> 37:23.190
NO, JORDAN! NO, OK?

37:23.200 --> 37:24.929
JUST, IT WAS MY FAULT, OK?

37:24.940 --> 37:26.362
YOU CAN'T JUST BLAME HIM.

37:26.370 --> 37:27.963
OLIVIA, YES, I CAN.

37:27.970 --> 37:29.278
NO, JORDAN.

37:29.280 --> 37:30.736
PLEASE PROMISE ME THAT YOU
WON'T SAY ANYTHING.

37:30.740 --> 37:33.380
LEILA DOESN'T KNOW, AND
IF SHE EVER FOUND OUT...

37:33.380 --> 37:35.371
PLEASE PROMISE ME.

37:35.380 --> 37:40.944
OK. I PROMISE. YEAH,
I WON'T SAY ANYTHING.

37:47.790 --> 37:48.951
HEY, LOOK AT ME.

37:48.960 --> 37:51.019
IT'S EMBARRASSING.

37:55.940 --> 37:59.831
IT'S OK. IT'S OK.

38:04.040 --> 38:12.040
WOMAN: MM MM MM

38:19.560 --> 38:22.359
MAN: I'M YOUNG,
AND I'M FOOLISH

38:22.360 --> 38:24.055
MADE BAD DECISIONS

38:24.060 --> 38:25.892
I BLOCK OUT THE NEWS

38:25.900 --> 38:28.562
TURNED MY BACK
ON RELIGION

38:28.570 --> 38:29.992
DON'T HAVE NO DEGREE

38:30.000 --> 38:31.638
I'M SOMEWHAT NAIVE

38:31.640 --> 38:35.270
I'VE MADE IT THIS FAR
ON MY OWN...

38:35.280 --> 38:37.635
I NEVER MEANT TO HURT YOU.

38:37.640 --> 38:38.744
NO.

38:38.750 --> 38:40.502
...AIN'T BEEN
GETTING ME HIGHER

38:40.510 --> 38:44.743
I LIFT UP MY HEAD,
AND THE WORLD IS ON FIRE

38:44.750 --> 38:47.811
WITH DREAD IN MY HEART
AND FEAR IN MY BONES...

38:47.820 --> 38:50.619
I'M READY TO LET HIM
GO NOW.

38:52.930 --> 38:55.399
I'VE GOT EVERYTHING
I NEED RIGHT HERE.

38:55.400 --> 38:59.098
...PRAY, PRAY

38:59.100 --> 39:00.170
GRACE: COME HERE.

39:00.170 --> 39:04.334
MAYBE I'll PRAY

39:04.340 --> 39:08.061
I HAVE NEVER BELIEVED
IN YOU, NO

39:08.070 --> 39:10.107
THAT I'M GONNA PRAY

39:10.110 --> 39:12.101
DAD? HEY! HA HA!

39:12.110 --> 39:15.102
HA! WHOA! HA!

39:15.110 --> 39:17.442
-HI.

39:17.450 --> 39:18.645
-OH, I'M GOOD.
-OH, I'M SO SORRY.

39:18.650 --> 39:20.118
I HOPE I DIDN'T
WAKE YOU UP.

39:20.120 --> 39:21.110
NO, NO, NO.

39:21.120 --> 39:22.758
WE JUST GOT IN EARLY.

39:22.760 --> 39:23.659
OH, WE?

39:23.660 --> 39:26.254
YEAH. I WANT YOU TO
MEET SOMEONE.

39:26.260 --> 39:28.354
OK.

39:28.360 --> 39:30.124
MAN: YOU WON'T FIND ME
IN CHURCH

39:30.130 --> 39:31.154
CHOIR: NO

39:31.160 --> 39:32.321
READING THE BIBLE

39:32.330 --> 39:33.866
NO

39:33.870 --> 39:37.261
I AM STILL HERE, AND I'M
STILL YOUR DISCIPLE

39:37.270 --> 39:39.136
I'M DOWN ON MY KNEES

39:39.140 --> 39:40.801
AND BEGGING YOU PLEASE

39:40.810 --> 39:44.576
I'M BROKEN, ALONE,
AND AFRAID

39:44.580 --> 39:46.639
I'M NOT A SAINT

39:46.650 --> 39:48.744
I'M MORE OF A SINNER

39:48.750 --> 39:50.377
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE...

39:51.650 --> 39:53.140
BUT I FEAR FOR
THE WINNERS

39:53.150 --> 39:55.187
WHEN I TRIED TO EXPLAIN

39:55.190 --> 39:57.181
THE WORDS RAN AWAY

39:58.660 --> 40:00.651
THAT'S WHY I AM SITTING
HERE TODAY

40:05.300 --> 40:06.927
YEAH.

40:06.930 --> 40:08.068
I CAME TO TALK.

40:08.070 --> 40:09.993
ABOUT WHAT?

40:12.010 --> 40:15.162
WHY'D YOU SHOW UP
AT MY HOUSE LIKE THAT

40:15.170 --> 40:17.172
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS?

40:18.580 --> 40:22.369
DON'T KNOW, REALLY.

40:22.380 --> 40:24.371
WHEN YOUR KIDS SHOWED UP
AROUND HERE,

40:24.380 --> 40:26.189
I THOUGHT THERE WAS
SOME HOPE

40:26.190 --> 40:27.589
WE COULD MEND THINGS.

40:27.590 --> 40:30.287
HOPE. WELL, HOW CAN
THERE BE ANY HOPE

40:30.290 --> 40:32.281
IF YOU STILL CAN'T
ACCEPT MY WIFE?

40:32.290 --> 40:33.849
SHE AIN'T ONE OF US, SON.

40:33.860 --> 40:36.192
I CAN ACCEPT YOU,
MY GRANDKIDS.

40:36.200 --> 40:37.690
OK, LOOK, I LOVE LAURA.

40:37.700 --> 40:41.364
SHE'S MY WIFE. SHE'S THE
MOTHER OF MY CHILDREN.

40:41.370 --> 40:43.737
IF YOU CAN'T LEARN
TO ACCEPT HER,

40:43.740 --> 40:46.107
THEN THERE'S NOTHING
LEFT TO TALK ABOUT.

40:48.140 --> 40:49.278
I GUESS WE'RE DONE HERE.

40:49.280 --> 40:51.135
I GUESS WE ARE.

40:52.380 --> 40:53.939
HOW'S THE KID HOLDING UP?

40:53.950 --> 40:56.715
YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT SPENCER?

40:56.720 --> 40:58.347
MM-HMM. DIDN'T TAKE
IT TOO WELL LAST NIGHT,

40:58.350 --> 40:59.749
DID HE?

40:59.750 --> 41:01.445
IT WAS JUST A SURPRISE,
THAT'S ALL.

41:01.450 --> 41:02.781
HE'LL BE FINE.

41:02.790 --> 41:07.125
YOU KNOW, YOUR OLD
FRIEND COREY JAMES,

41:07.130 --> 41:08.689
HE CAME AROUND HERE

41:08.700 --> 41:11.397
BEFORE HE SPLIT TOWN
YEARS BACK.

41:11.400 --> 41:15.166
SURE HAD A LOT
TO SAY.

41:20.910 --> 41:23.936
AND IF THAT WAS
SPENCER'S REACTION

41:23.940 --> 41:27.308
TO YOU DATING GRACIE
IN HIGH SCHOOL,

41:27.310 --> 41:30.519
